reviewText: At a time when WWE/WWF was on the ropes with the whole Bret Hart "Montreal Screwjob" scandal, WCW had the chance to totally bury them and BLEW IT big time! This was a sign of what was to come only 3 years later.I'll talk as I go, here is the card:Eddie Guerrero Vs. Dean Malenko (WCW Cruiserweight Championship) - This was the opener and was a very good one. The late, great Guerrero wins against the vaunted "Man Of 1,000 Holds" after a Frog Splash on both his torso and his leg which Eddie worked over for most of their match.Randy Savage, Vincent & Scott Norton Vs. Ray Traylor (The Big Bossman) & The Steiner Brothers - Slow but had its moments. The nWo trio wins after Savage's top rope elbow drop nails Scott Steiner.Goldberg Vs. Steve McMichael - In pretty much a 5 minute squash, Goldberg overpowers the former Horsemen!Saturn Vs. Chris Benoit (Raven's Rules match) - Originally, Raven was supposed to wrestle but sent in Saturn instead. These two had a very good contest but the numbers game caught up with Benoit as Raven and his Flock ganged up on Benoit, allowing Saturn to get the win by submission with his "Rings Of Saturn."Buffy Bagwell Vs. Lex Luger - Not a horrible match but not a very good one either. Ends when Norton comes out and knocks Luger out with brass knuckles to give Bagwell the win.DDP Vs. Curt Hennig (WCW U.S. Title Match) - Originally scheduled to be Ric Flair Vs. Hennig in a cage but Flair injured himself and was unable to compete so DDP stepped in. Not a great bout but certainly not the worst as DDP wins with his "Diamond Cutter" (later known as "Twist Of Fate" or "RKO") for the win and the title.Larry Zbyszko Vs. Eric Bischoff - This was for the control of Monday Nitro (yawn!). The premise sucked but the match itself wasn't too bad. Was mostly Zbyszko giving Bischoff a good beating. Ends when special referee Bret Hart awards the win to Larry due to constant interference from Scott Hall AND trapping Hall in his "Sharpshooter" deathlock!Sting Vs. Hulk Hogan (WCW World Title Match) - This match is what buried the whole card! I would've loved to have known what the undercard cats were thinking because I know I would've been p*ssed if I was them! I mean, think about it, you put in all that work to put on a good show and then the two marquee guys basically (to put it bluntly) f**k it up!Anyway, the match wasn't very good to begin with and then that botched 3 count at the end when it was clear that ref Nick Patrick DID NOT fast count (thus screwing up the screw job ending and making Bret Hart look stupid)!The card, to be honest, could've been one of the better cards in wrestling history but thanks to the main event, it'll be remembered as the beginning of the end of WCW.My personal recommendation is that if you pick this tape up, please only look at up until Zbyszko/Bischoff! Yeah, that's bad when a gimmick match is better than your main event!
summary: One of the worst cards in wrestling history!

reviewText: Not a bad show, too many guys got replaced, it would have been nice to see Nash vs Giant, Raven vs Benoit, Konnan, Norton, and Savage vs Steiners and Bossman, but still not too shabby of a show. The main event was  disappointing, but I still got my money's worth.
summary: Perhaps one of the best of 1997

reviewText: The cruiserweight title match between Eddie Guerrero & Dean Malenko was a hot opener but not their best work. The 6 man tag team match between Team NWO(Scott Norton,Vincent & Randy Savage) & Team WCW(Ray Traylor,Rick Steiner & Scott Steiner) was not great but pretty good. The Bill Goldberg-Steve McMichael match was not good but at least it was fairly short. The Perry Saturn-Chris Benoit-Raven's Rules match while not a bad bout,the stupid rules eliminated any chance of a good match too. The Buff Bagwell-Lex Luger match stinks like a 27-year old hamburger. The US title match between Curt Henning & DDP was 10 minutes of nothing. The Larry Zbyszko-Eric Bischoff match was horrible. The World title match between Hulk Hogan & Sting was short,awful & stupid. I give this PPV a 2 out of 10.

reviewText: This video can be summed up very quickly, if you like listening to dusty rhodes babble and fumble up on the mic you'll enjoys as he goes overboard about just how important this event is and quote "fate has brought us here today for this very reason"  yeah I'm sure.  After a few minutes I found myself blocking out the announcers and watching teh matches which are good with DDP and Henning being very good but as usual the main events in WCW are terrible hogan get a clean win over sting and then bret hart starts the match over again for no reason and hogan finally job's doesn't make much sense but then again neither did WCW. At the end all teh wrestlers come out from the back and celebrate, like I'm sure they really wanted to miss there flights to be there from that.  Speaking of which if you watch the proceading WCW SUPERBRAWL you'll find bret hart turns on Sting, as Tony Schavonie yells "It was a plot from the get go"  which leaves you thinking what was the point?
summary: Highs, lows, then it plundges dramatically.

Misprints also occured with the covers and labels for Starrcade 1995, 1996, World War 3 1995, 1996, 1997.
